OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAsthma 'not an exemption   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffrom wearing masks'        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Most people with asthma or chronic     
OL,6, obstructive pulmonary disease should   
OL,7, wear face masks when required, the     
OL,8, British Medical Association has said.  
OL,10,FThe guidance from NI Direct states     
OL,11,Fpeople with such conditions only need  
OL,12,Fto say they cannot wear a mask when    
OL,13,Fasked to prove they are exempt.        
OL,15,F"Ninety nine per cent of people who    
OL,16,Fhave those conditions can wear a face  
OL,17,Fmask," said the BMA's Dr Alan Stout.   
OL,19,FMasks are mandatory in a number of     
OL,20,Fsettings including public transport.   
